                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1351">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 412.11/36.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Ambassador</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Renew request for extension of time for filing claims before Claims Commission to
                    January 1, 1912. The time originally fixed <pb facs="1064" n="948"
                        xml:id="pg_948"/> seems to the Department too short, as claimants naturally
                    first presented their claims to this Government, and some have not been able to
                    present claims after receiving definite information regarding the Commission,
                    and furthermore the Department has been unable, after consulting claimants
                    concerning their desires as to submission of claims to the Commission, to
                    forward them to the Embassy within the fixed time. The short extension suggested
                    by the Department would, in its opinion, permit the presentation of claims by
                    all those wishing to present them, and would avoid any possible difficulties
                    regarding them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
